{
  "stem": "9899.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So she took the Star of David off of us and took us, with a little suitcase and her last fur coat, because of the-- to cover us in-- in the cold, and we went straight to the train station.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The train station in [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Limburg ?] was a beautiful, glass-domed station, very similar to the one in London.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it had poles holding up the sky-- the dome, the glass dome.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When we got to the station, of each of those poles hang a person, a Jew, with a big sign saying, this is what happens to the Jews who dare to escape.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They are hanged on the spot.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I saw that, and I trembled, and I held onto my mother's hand.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she said, not to be afraid, just walk.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She had left behind all the papers, all pictures that might identify us, all our passes, all our ration cards, everything at all that might point a finger to us.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She had sewn into her girdle the last of the jewels.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And with that, we left the [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Limburger ?] ghetto.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And to this day, and 1943 when the ghetto was closed, I believe that we are the only survivors of that-- that were left alive from the [?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Limburger ?] ghetto.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I have never come across to another person who stayed and survived till the end.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We boarded the first train that came without knowing where it was going to.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We were on the train for about half an hour when they came to inspect the papers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My mother had nothing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The three of us were lying on the floor-- it was a-- a train for cattle, it was a cattle train-- covered with that fur coat.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The German came.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
